Wondering why your QR code expired? It shouldn't.
For websites, Google Forms, event registrations, and most university-related uses, always use static QR codes. They are free, reliable, and continue working indefinitely because the destination link is stored directly in the QR code. A simple and free tool for generating static QR codes is:
https://goqr.me/
Be careful when searching online for QR code generators. Many websites generate dynamic QR codes by default, or only offer dynamic QR codes. These rely on a third-party redirection service and often require an ongoing subscription. If the subscription expires, your QR code may stop working.
Before printing or sharing a QR code, test it to ensure it works correctly.
